title: Space Development Agency’s first launch slips to March due to satellite glitch
summary: The first launch of the Space Development Agency’s constellation planned for mid-December will slip to March 2023 due to an anomaly detected in York Space’s satellites.

title: Japanese billionaire selects crew for circumlunar Starship flight
summary: A Japanese billionaire has selected an eclectic group of people who will accompany him on a SpaceX Starship flight around the moon, although it remains uncertain when that mission will take place.

title: NASA preparing for Orion splashdown to conclude Artemis 1
summary: NASA’s Orion spacecraft is in the home stretch of the Artemis 1 uncrewed test flight as the agency prepares for the vehicle’s ultimate test: reentry and splashdown in the Pacific Ocean.
